{"key":"post-5395100","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5395100</id>\n<content>Even at their best, I've found the electronic hygrometers to be mediocre in performance.  You can find a decent, cheap mechanical hygrometer at cigar shops and pet stores.  Calibrate by wrapping in a damp towel for an hour, then unwrap and adjust the screw on the back so the dial reads 98%.  Repeat calibration monthly, as they drift.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>5394939</prev>\n<first>5394643</first>\n<last>5395100</last>\n<when>1142278217</when>\n<utime>03/13/06 09:30 PM</utime>\n</post>"}